transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks a lot, Viagra Quinn speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, my name is Johnny Riddle. I want to cancel my account.

Speaker 1: All right. Give me one moment. Let me pull up your account.

Speaker 2: You did say Mr. Riddle, correct?

Speaker 1: Yes, it is.

Speaker 2: All right. And I do see you are a VIP here with us, sir.

Speaker 1: Do you mind if I ask why you no longer want the Viagra?

Speaker 2: Yeah, it don't work.

Speaker 1: Oh, wow. Okay. Well, definitely don't want to get something that's not working for you.

Speaker 2: You know what we can do? Obviously stop sending you that one and get you another one.

Speaker 1: I don't want another one. I don't want another one because I don't think they're going to work anyway.

Speaker 2: And any particular reason why you think that?

Speaker 1: They didn't even try.

Speaker 2: They what?

Speaker 1: They didn't even try to work.

Speaker 2: Okay. I mean, this is a body chemistry thing.

Speaker 1: That's why we're sending you a completely different pill because clearly that one didn't work.

Speaker 2: No, I don't want another one. I just want to cancel it.

Speaker 1: And it would be for free.

Speaker 2: No, I don't want another one.

Speaker 1: All right. And you do know you can order this as needed too, correct?

Speaker 2: Pardon me?

Speaker 1: You do know you can order this as needed?

Speaker 2: I just don't want it.

Speaker 1: All right. Well, you will not receive it again, sir. We'll cancel you out.

Speaker 2: All right. Thank you, sir.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: You too. Bye-bye.
